<br>
Verant did change this and gave level 60 warriors a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> chance</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> to taunt mobs up to level 65.<br>
<br>
Problem is that chance, is just that, and its a pretty low percentage chance at that.<br>
<br>
Problem with this is the DPS setup that verant made where warriors are the base class at 100%, monks at 120%, and rogues at 140%. Rangers are somewhere at 95%, and the Knight classes are below rangers.<br>
<br>
Now its hard to even have a chance for warriors to taunt since we well know that a monk easily is above 120% DPS that of a warrior and rogues are closer to 200% of a warrior. In other words, monks/rogues and other melee are so far ahead of what they should be according to verant, that the chance warriors get to taunt is not a chance at all.<br>
<br>
The Damage guidelines Verant has set, which Im sure Tuant is tied in, is outdated to todays weaponry.<br>
<br>
If Verant has no intention of fixing Taunt then at least they can rework the Damage guidelines they set and short of reducing monk/rogue damage the only thing they can do is increase warrior damage to be back in line with <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> their vision</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
<br>
Once again, I've not seen any of our 60 monks do only 120%, or our 60 Rogues do 140%, at any of our raids unless they forgot to hit attack.<br>
<br>
Since warrior weaponry is limited in terms of warriors go with weaponry that may not have higher DPS but have higher agro, ie EB/procs. Because of this, unless verant decides to come out with warrior only high DPS high taunting weaponry, which I doubt, the only other solution I see is to give warriors some kind of new damage table or some other, that will increase damage output so that warriors are at least back in line with verants original vision of their Damage guidelines.<br>
<br>
Once again, nothing new has been asked, raise warrior DPS so that monk/rogue damage isn't so far ahead of warrior DPS as it stands now. Fix what is so obviously broken.<br>
<br>
There are many other issues such as AC/Armor/HPs/etc that other knight and monk classes are closing in on but my post has already been to long, and will leave that for another time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
